The paper deals with a problem of clustering in a hypergraph stochastic block model, which is a topic related to data mining (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a spectral algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of spectral methods (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the probability of exact recovery, which is a topic related to statistical inference (cs.SD) and information theory (cs.IT).
